(secondQuint)Partial Liver Radiotherapy for Unresectable Liver Metastases.

 The purpose of this study is to evaluate safety and feasibility of conformal radiation therapy in patients with metastatic colorectal liver cancer.

 This study would also evaluate local control rate within irradiated area and to assess failure patterns and survival of patients treated with conformal liver radiation.

